{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionVast quantities of data are required for state-of-the-art machine learning algorithms.",
    "However, the data cannot be uploaded to a central server or cloud due to sheer volume, privacy, or legislative reasons.",
    "Federated learning (FL) [1], also known as collaborative learning, has been the subject of many studies.",
    "FL adopts a distributed machine learning architecture with a central server for model aggregation, where clients themselves update the machine learning model.",
    "Clients can maintain ownership of their data, i.e., upload only the updated model to the central server and not expose any of their private data.The federated learning paradigm addresses several challenges."
  ]
}